creator: librivoxbooks
description:
LibriVox's Short Poetry Collection 116. This is a collection of 25 poems read by LibriVox volunteers for January 2013. This project contains the following: Annabel Lee by Edgar Allan Poe (1809-1849)
Apology by Amy Lowell (1874-1925)
The Atlantic by Edward Doyle (1854-?)
Benjamin Painter by Edgar Lee Masters (1868-1950)
Mrs. Benjamin Painter by Edgar Lee Masters (1868-1950)
Casey At the Bat by Ernest Lawrence Thayer (1860-1940)
Dark Spirit of Desart Rude by Percy Shelley (1792-1822)
Exeunt Omnes by Thomas Hardy (1840-1928)
The Fool Errant by Amy Lowell (1874-1925)
Hope is the thing with feathers by Emily Dickinson (1830-1886)
Kubla Khan by Samuel Taylor Coleridge (1772-1834)
Learning to Read by Frances E.W. Harper (1825-1911)
Leonardo’s “Monna Lisa” by Edward Dowden (1843-1913)
Music I Heard by Conrad Aiken (1889-1973)
Mute Opinion by Thomas Hardy (1840-1928)
Old Souls by Thomas Gordon Hake (1809-1894)
Potato Bug Exterminators by James McIntyre (1828-1906)
The Rainbow by Vine Colby (?-?)
The Service Flag by William Herschell (1873-1939)
A Sonnet of the Moon by Charles Best (1570-1627)
The Dancing Girl by James Weldon Johnson (1871-1938)
Think Gently of the Erring by Julia A. (Fletcher) Carney (1823-1908)
Vitae Summa Brevis Spem Nos Vetat Incohare Longam by Ernest Dowson (1867-1900)
The Wanderer by Zoe Akins (1886-1958)
Warren's Address to the American Soldiers by John Pierpont (1785-1866) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

M4B format available
